JOHANNESBURG, September 14  – The Premier Soccer League will observe a moment of silence for the late former UN Secretary General Kofi Annan, the late Uthongathi Chairman Nicholas Gumede and former player Reggie Jantjies. This will apply at all Premiership, National First Division and MultiChoice Diski Challenge fixtures on Saturday and Sunday this weekend. The funeral service of the globally respected former diplomat, Annan, was held in Ghana on Thursday. Gumede, the chairman of Uthongathi FC in the National First Division, passed on this week and will be buried on Sunday, at Tongaat Town Hall. The late Reggie Jantjies, formerly with Cape Town Spurs and Hellenic FC, passed on this week. The Premier Soccer League remembers all three men for their contribution to football and humanity. (ANA)